==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[symmetria]]'', originally from Greek ''[[συμμετρία]]'' (''[[symmetria]]''). ''sym'' means ''like'' and ''metria'' means ''measure''; i.e. ''like measure'' or ''similar measurement''.

===Noun===
'''symmetry'''  {{uncountable}}

# Exact [[correspondence]] on either side of a [[dividing]] [[line]], [[plane]], [[centre]] or [[axis]].
# The [[satisfying]] [[arrangement]] of a [[balanced]] [[distribution]] of the [[element]]s of a whole.

